      "content": "I hear you on the generalization thing, definitely don't want to go down that road. But if I'm preparing field staff, I need to understand the nuances of the \"social landscape\" you mentioned. For example, if we're looking at regions where certain groups are more traditionally nomadic vs. sedentary, doesn't that create a specific kind of cultural friction or different ways of handling authority that I should account for? It feels like just looking at \"power structures\" might miss some of the more ingrained ways these people actually live and relate to one another.",
